The paper deals with information theory and communication games, which are central topics in the field of information theory (cs.IT). It also involves game theory and optimization, which are relevant to the sub-category of computational game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses compression and communication, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents an extension to decentralized stochastic control, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
